.Sh DESCRIPTION
Prints the IDs in the vault, one per line: every scope by default, or every shared-pool entry with --shared. It is the quick "what's in here" verb - a bare inventory of names. For per-scope detail (secret counts, key kinds, drift), use 'sharibako status'.

No age key is required; 'list' reads directory names only and never decrypts. --json emits a plain array of IDs.

EXAMPLES

List every scope:
  sharibako list

List the shared pool (targets for 'link'):
  sharibako list --shared

Machine-readable:
  sharibako list --json
